{"word":"H1699 - דֹּבֶר - dôber - do'-ber - Fold","slug":"H1699","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דֹּבֶר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dôber"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>do'-ber"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Fold"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05E8;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D1;&#x05E8; - do&#x0302;ber  dibbe&#x0302;r</b> - <i>do'-ber, dib-bare'</i><p/>The first form is from <a href=\"#/H1696\">H1696</a> (in its original sense); a <i>pasture</i> (from its <i>arrangement</i> of the flock); translated <i>fold</i> or <i>manner</i>. The second form is for <a href=\"#/H1697\">H1697</a>; translated <i>word: - </i>fold, manner."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1682\">H1682</a>, <a href=\"#/H1683\">H1683</a>, <a href=\"#/H1687\">H1687</a>, <a href=\"#/H1688\">H1688</a>, <a href=\"#/H1696\">H1696</a>, <a href=\"#/H1697\">H1697</a>, <a href=\"#/H1698\">H1698</a>, <a href=\"#/H1700\">H1700</a>, <a href=\"#/H1702\">H1702</a>, <a href=\"#/H1703\">H1703</a>, <a href=\"#/H1704\">H1704</a>, <a href=\"#/H1705\">H1705</a>, <a href=\"#/H4057\">H4057</a>"}]}